
1. Install Cygwin

2. Run Cygwin first time and perform post-install activity

3. Copy the content of Cygwin home dir to new home dir in tea-set
find | xargs tar -cf - | ( cd "NEW-HOME-DIR" ; tar -xf - )

4. Remove the current home dir
cd ..
rm -rf "$HOME"

5. Create soft link to NEW-HOME-DIR
ln -s "NEW-HOME-DIR" $USER

6. Close the current Cygwin session

